text: Spokane county is a county in the U.S. state of Washington. Its county seat is Spokane, Washington. As of 2020, 539,339 people live in the county. The county has 1,764 square miles, or 4,569 square kilometers, of land, and it was organized in 1858. ==References== Category:1858 establishments in the United States Category:1850s establishments in Washington (state)
title: Spokane County, Washington
